article.description: — John Carter Jr. had 14 points as Navy easily defeated Lafayette 68-44 on Monday night.
article.headline: Carter Jr. scores 14 to lift Navy over Lafayette 68-44
article.linkText: Carter Jr. scores 14 to lift Navy over Lafayette 68-44
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- — John Carter Jr. had 14 points as Navy easily defeated Lafayette 68-44 on Monday night. Greg Summers had 11 points, seven rebounds and six assists for Navy (16-8, 9-4 Patriot League). Tyler Nelson added 11 points. Richard Njoku had 10 points. Lafayette totaled 14 second-half points, a season low for the team. Neal Quinn had 14 points and seven rebounds for the Leopards (7-15, 4-7). The Midshipmen improve to 2-0 against the Leopards for the season. Navy defeated Lafayette 69-55 on Jan. 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
